 <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/02 7:56:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2557.topic&index=41>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: enrage</span><hr size=1> Your job, as the tank, is to control the mob. It's what you do. You take a mob. You engage it. You position it. You hold its attention. It's what a warrior does.<br>
<br>
I can't think of a single non-raid situation where you would be better off pinning a mob rather than keeping it in the open. Wall agro, poofing, LOS issues with spells and archery, 'You cannot see your target' messages and melee/pet push all argue conclusively AGAINST pinning a mob.<br>
<br>
With that said, how hard is it to engage a mob 15 feet out from camp, in the open, engage it, gain some agro, and then strafe 180 degrees so it's back is to the group, thus signalling that &quot;I have good agro, this mob is yours to do with what you wish&quot;? It's not. It's your job. Do it.<br>
<br>
If you lose agro every once in a while, sit. If you lose it consistently, figure out why and fix it. If people don't listen to why you don't tash before the mob is engaged, or drop huge bombs during enrage, leave. It's that simple. It worked for me when I was in Treeweave and GJBS/Wraith Bone Hammer and it works for me now. <br>
<br>
Encounter control and awareness is the name of the game, at every level.  Performing simple actions to maximize the capabilities of a group or raid is your responsibility. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65044"><b><i>Kromagnon</b></i></a> - Overlord<br><a href="http://www.evguild.org">The Elitists and Vagrants</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glatius2>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 608<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/02 8:03:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2557.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: enrage</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If you lose agro every once in a while, sit. If you lose it consistently, figure out why and fix it. If people don't listen to why you don't tash before the mob is engaged, or drop huge bombs during enrage, leave. It's that simple. It worked for me when I was in Treeweave and GJBS/Wraith Bone Hammer and it works for me now. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
